    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Seals stamped on books and prints indicating that the work has been approved by a censor for publication. Prime examples are censor's seals on Japanese prints dating from the 18th-19th centuries.</Note_Text>
